,Recommended,529440,33682171,Posted: 20 July,all,Ashpolt,"It's great to finally see an accurate football simulation after all these years of the ""big names"" getting the most basic things wrong. I mean, I get why they used to show rectangular pitches when the first football games were released back on the Playstation 2 in the 1960s, but it's 2017 now guys, rendering realistic circular pitches is doable now! Don't get me started on the underlying homophobia that causes Fifa et al to omit showing the umpire kissing the scoring player. And for the love of god, when will people learn how to spell ""goldkeeper""?These problems and several more are fixed in Behold the Kickmen, surely the most realistic football game that will ever be released, and also surely the pinnacle of Dan Marshall's game dev career. Any other accomplishments before or after this are rendered meaningless. When he dies, his gravestone will surely be adorned with a ball, and a sign proclaiming him to be truly the kickiest of all the mans."
