76561198017503702,Recommended,529440,34733067,Posted: 4 September,all,agemame,"A solid 7? I'd go a bit higherIf you've read any of the reviews and the preamble on this page you'll have picked up on the conceit here, that it's a football game written by a non football fan who didn't do the research. And yet, you get the feeling that that may not be strictly true...Certainly the general feel of the title is that of a less polished Sensible Soccer or Kick Off type title - both stalwarts of the arcade football genre. That the rules are quite blatantly wrong seems if anything to make things more accessible, the offside rule in particular.My main gripe therefore is with the fact that this is only single player - the idea of having a knockabout with a more straightfaced FIFA or PES fan would make for a great experience, as the initial joke game feel gives way to something more arcadey. However, I can see how two player control in this setup would rapidly become unwieldy, as the ball moves very quickly, particularly in later matches.I realise in this that I haven't covered the Story mode, which is the key to this game as currently set up. It's all a bit Speed Racer and manga in styling, with an overblown melodrama that suits this game to the ground. If football doesn't appeal, the secret future deathsport mode is worth a look, somehow combining the gameplay with a style more akin to early Bitmap Brothers titles (you know which one I mean).One thing I would say though is do the tutorial mode first - for an arcade title, the controls can be a bit finicky compared to the one button and a stick approach of the aforementioned Kick Off type games. But yes, don't think of this as just a joke game, there is something of substance under the surface."
